Name Test/Libraries/List/isEmpty
Synopsis Test whether a list is empty.
Function bool isEmpty(list[&T] lst)
Usage import List;
Description Returns true when a list is empty and false otherwise.
Examples 
rascal>import List;
ok
rascal>isEmpty([]);
bool: true
rascal>isEmpty([1, 2, 3]);
bool: false
